My guess is that it wasn't about promoting Apache HTTPD as such, but about promoting open source software in general.
The web was the first part of the information technology world where open source software rose to a dominant position,
so it might have been like saying that if the web runs on open source, there's no reason everything else can't.
While it might have been the subconscious thought, I think many people added that button just for the sake of completeness
though.
</p>

