<h3>Programming languages and databases</h3>

<p>
At the end of the web 1.0 era, making static websites was no longer cool, and people started to generate
pages dynamically even if their content didn't change any often.
People tend to have even stronger opinions about programming languages than operating systems,
which was definitely reflected in promotional buttons.
</p>
<p>
Relational database software was never excluded from the debate, and the buttons either.
MySQL and Firebird still provide official buttons on their websites. Even more curiously,
MariaDB, which is a relatively recent fork of MySQL, continued the tradition and made new
official buttons, even though I'm still to see anyone use them.
